2. Object

Definition:
An object is an instance of a class. It represents a real-world entity and contains actual data.

Example:

s1 = Student("Guru", 21)

3. Reference Variable

Definition:
A reference variable stores the address (reference) of an object in memory and is used to access that object.

Example:

s1 = Student("Guru", 21)

Here, s1 is a reference variable that refers to the Student object.


class student:
